# User Rules

## Communication

- Always respond in Traditional Chinese.
- Keep responses concise and practical.
- When giving commands, prefer copy-ready command blocks.

## Go Project Conventions

- Use clear and consistent naming for handlers, tests, and files.
- Keep HTTP handlers simple; move complex logic into helper functions.
- Add tests for new behavior when practical.

## Docker and CI Conventions

- Keep Docker image builds reproducible and minimal.
- Ensure CI checks can run with `go test ./...` and `go build ./cmd/api`.
- Prefer small, focused workflow steps with clear names.

